parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Takata airbag inflator can cause serious injury or death, and the delay or refusal to perform the recall can jeopardize the safety of the vehicle occupants.
symptoms: the airbag does not deploy in a crash

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unavailability of recall parts can delay the repair, leaving the vehicle occupants at risk of serious injury or death.
symptoms: the airbag does not deploy in a crash
and the vehicle is not repaired due to the unavailability of parts.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The refusal of the dealer to perform the recall can jeopardize the safety of the vehicle occupants and leave them at risk of serious injury or death.
symptoms: The dealer refuses to perform the recall
and the airbag warning lamp illuminates.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the cooling fan motor can cause the engine to overheat, leading to engine failure, smoke, and even fires, which can result in accidents or damage to the vehicle.
symptoms: The temperature sensor flashes an incorrect reading
smoke emits from the bottom of the motor

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the cam shaft sensor can cause the vehicle to stall, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: the check engine light comes on

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to not start, which can leave the driver stranded.
The failure of the temperature sensor can cause incorrect readings, which can lead to engine damage or overheating.
symptoms: The temperature sensor flashes an incorrect reading.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission to engage in reverse gear can cause accidents, especially when reversing out of parking spaces or driveways, and can lead to costly repairs.
symptoms: The vehicle fails to engage in reverse gear
the vehicle suddenly stops or becomes stuck in gear.
